  "prompt": "Are there any antibiotics that can be purchased over the counter?",
  "response": "In the United States, there are no oral antibiotics available over the counter (OTC). All antibiotics require a prescription from a licensed healthcare provider. This is to prevent misuse, antibiotic resistance, and potential side effects. However, there are some topical antibiotic ointments and creams that can be purchased OTC, such as:\n\n1. Bacitracin\n2. Neosporin (contains neomycin, polymyxin B, and bacitracin)\n3. Polysporin\n\nThese are typically used for minor cuts, scrapes, and burns to prevent infection. For oral antibiotics, you must consult a healthcare professional who can diagnose your condition and prescribe the appropriate medication.",
